It is possible to read a nested xml tag with an [incremental reading](https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-dataformat-xml): basically you have to create an [`XMLStreamReader`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/javax/xml/stream/XMLStreamReader.html) streamreader and set it manually so that points to the `Element2` nested tag. Your xmlmapper will read the nested tag using the pointing xmlstreamreader like below:

~~~
@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)
public class Element2 {
    @JacksonXmlProperty(isAttribute = true)
    private String attribute;
}


File xml = new File(&quot;msg.xml&quot;);
XMLInputFactory f = XMLInputFactory.newFactory();
XMLStreamReader sr = f.createXMLStreamReader(new FileInputStream(xml));
XmlMapper mapper = new XmlMapper();
sr.nextTag(); //&lt;--point to Element1
sr.nextTag(); //&lt;--point to Element2
//now you can deserialize the nested xml tag
Element2 element2 = mapper.readValue(sr, Element2.class);
sr.close(); //&lt;-- closing the stream
~~~

